                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1531/13a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-30T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 30, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Department’s telegram 41, August 18, 3 p.m. Please inquire of the Honduran
                    Government whether it is prepared to initiate exploratory conversations at an
                    early date. Since this Government is planning to give public notice shortly of
                    the intention to negotiate agreements with other Central American countries it
                    seems appropriate to inquire as a matter of courtesy whether the Honduran
                    Government desires a similar announcement to be made with respect to that
                    country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
